article.headline: Colorado 91, Alcorn St. 51
article.story: BOULDER, Colo. -- Alec Burks scored 22 points, his fourth straight game scoring 20 or more, to lead Colorado to a 91-51 victory over Alcorn State on Tuesday night. Marcus Relphorde added 15 points and Cory Higgins 16 for the Buffaloes (2-2). Marquiz Baker led the Braves (0-4) with 13 points. Alcorn State took their only lead, 10-8, early in the game on a 3-pointer by Baker. But the Buffaloes outscored them 20-0 during the next five minutes, which included successive 3-pointers by Relphorde and Burks. Colorado was up 49-27 at halftime and led by as many as 43 points in the second half. They finished shooting 47.8 percent from the field and outrebounded the Braves 50-36.
